## Practice Tips

### 1. Build Projects
Start with small projects:
- Portfolio website
- Product landing page
- Blog layout
- E-commerce grid
- Responsive dashboard

### 2. Recreate Popular Designs
Try to recreate:
- YouTube layout
- Twitter card
- Facebook timeline
- Medium articles
- Dribbble designs

### 3. Solve Layout Challenges
Practice specific tasks:
- Centered modals
- Sticky headers
- Responsive grids
- Card layouts
- Form styling

### 4. Experiment with Properties
Use browser dev tools to:
- Toggle properties on/off
- Edit values in real-time
- Test different selectors
- Inspect computed styles
- Debug spacing issues

### 5. Read Other People's Code
Learn from:
- Open source projects
- Popular websites
- GitHub repositories
- CSS frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind)
- Design systems

